SIMPLE: sagamore
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sagamore
<hw>Sag"a*more</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Sachem</er>.]</ety> <def>The head of a tribe among the American
Indians; a chief; -- generally used as synonymous with
<xex>sachem</xex>, but some writers distinguished between them, making
the <xex>sachem</xex> a chief of the first rank, and a
<xex>sagamore</xex> one of the second rank.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Be it
<xex>sagamore</xex>, sachem, or powwow.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Longfellow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A juice used in medicine.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sagapen</ent>⟦br⟧
